channel.description:
Hey peeps, I’m backs and I taught why not sharing this with the community. This could be not the right way to do it, but it works, and it’s my way. After completing this tutorial you will understand a lot more of PI’s itemclicking.
If u don't like the way this is done don't troll on this topic, please comment if u used :)

[B]This tutorial also inludes clanchat messaging (only when the owner is rolling the dice).[/B]
Credits: 
Me for the itemclicking part, dicing, clanchat message sending etc.
Chaoticblitz for the dialogue part and switching dies.

Before we get started, you must know that the messages I used are probably different than the ones on Runescape, u can change them if u like, so first of all go to Clickitem.java and declare these:
[code]
import server.world.ClanChatHandler;
import server.util.Misc;
import server.Server;
[/code]
And these:
[code]
int Diceamount1 = Misc.random(6);
int Diceamount2 = Misc.random(100);
int Diceamount3 = Misc.random(10);
int DiceamountB1 = Misc.random(6);
int DiceamountB2 = Misc.random(6);
int DiceamountB3 = Misc.random(6);
int DiceamountB4 = Misc.random(6);
int DiceamountB = (DiceamountB1) + (DiceamountB2) + (DiceamountB3) + (DiceamountB4);
[/code]
Also add this:
[code]
if(itemId == 15084) {
c.getDH().sendDialogues(94, 4289);
}
[/code]
And these:
[code]
if (itemId == 15098 && System.currentTimeMillis() - c.diceDelay >= 5000) { //Dice 100
c.startAnimation(11900);
c.gfx0(2075);
c.sendMessage("I have rolled a "+ Diceamount2 +" on the amount dice.");
c.diceDelay = System.currentTimeMillis();
}
if (itemId == 15086 && System.currentTimeMillis() - c.diceDelay >= 5000) { //Dice 6
c.startAnimation(11900);
c.gfx0(2075);
c.sendMessage("I have rolled a "+ Diceamount1 +" on the amount die.");
c.diceDelay = System.currentTimeMillis();
}
if (itemId == 15088 && System.currentTimeMillis() - c.diceDelay >= 5000) { //Dice blackjack
c.startAnimation(11900);
c.gfx0(2075);
c.sendMessage("I have rolled a "+ DiceamountB +" on the amount die.");
c.diceDelay = System.currentTimeMillis();
}
if (itemId == 15092 && System.currentTimeMillis() - c.diceDelay >= 5000) { //Dice 10
c.startAnimation(11900);
c.gfx0(2075);
c.sendMessage("I have rolled a "+ Diceamount3 +" on the amount die.");
c.diceDelay = System.currentTimeMillis();
}
[/code]

Now open up Itemclick2.java and declare these:
[code]
int Diceamount1 = Misc.random(6);
int Diceamount2 = Misc.random(100);
int Diceamount3 = Misc.random(10);
int DiceamountB1 = Misc.random(6);
int DiceamountB2 = Misc.random(6);
int DiceamountB3 = Misc.random(6);
int DiceamountB4 = Misc.random(6);
int DiceamountB = (DiceamountB1) + (DiceamountB2) + (DiceamountB3) + (DiceamountB4);
[/code]
And add these under switch (itemId):
[code]
case 15098:
if (c.clanId < 0) {
c.sendMessage("You're not in a clanchat.");
return;
}
if(c.clanId >= 0 && Server.clanChat.clans[c.clanId].owner.equalsIgnoreCase(c.playerName) && System.currentTimeMillis() - c.diceDelay >= 5000) {
c.startAnimation(11900);
c.gfx0(2075);
c.sendMessage("I have rolled a "+ Diceamount2 +" on the amount dice.");
c.diceDelay = System.currentTimeMillis();
Server.clanChat.messageToClan("" + c.playerName + " rolled a "+ Diceamount2 +" on the amount dice.", c.clanId);
} else
c.sendMessage("Only the owner of the clan has the power to do that.");
break;
case 15086:
if (c.clanId < 0) {
